    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So it's basically just accepted as a reality then. But I've read some stuff arguing that the UN's inability to act in places like Gaza or Ukraine actually undermines its whole purpose and makes its claim to legitimacy pretty questionable. Do historians generally agree that these failures call its legitimacy into question, or is that considered a fringe argument?",
